latestPosts.caption:
We spoke to our senior leadership about what it truly means to work at a space where inclusion isn’t just a policy—it’s a way of life.

From boardrooms to back offices, from daily operations to long-term vision, The LaLiT stands committed to building a workplace where every identity is valued and every voice is heard.

In order of appearance:
Mr. Vivek Shukla – CEO, The LaLiT
Mr. Akshay Tyagi – Head, Diversity, Equity & Inclusion (DEI)
Mr. Vijay Bhalla – GM, The LaLiT New Delhi
Mr. Ashish Singh Bhau – Rooms Division Manager
Ms. Poonam Tyagi – Corporate HR
Ms. Amrita Bhadury – Corporate Marketing & Communications Manager
Ms. Monika Dutt Sharma – Head of Loyalty

Each of them echoed one truth: when people feel seen, safe, and celebrated—they thrive.

At The LaLiT, we honour every story, every identity, and every journey. Here, inclusion means embracing everyone just as they are—and celebrating them, every single day.

#ComeAsYouAre
#TheLalit
#InclusionAtWork
#LeadershipVoices
#DEI #PurLove

𝐈𝐟 𝐲𝐨𝐮’𝐯𝐞 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫 𝐟𝐞𝐥𝐭 𝐮𝐧𝐬𝐞𝐞𝐧, 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐨𝐧𝐞’𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐲𝐨𝐮.

𝐊𝐞𝐬𝐡𝐚𝐯 𝐒𝐮𝐫𝐢, 𝐄𝐱𝐞𝐜𝐮𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐃𝐢𝐫𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐨𝐫 𝐚𝐭 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐋𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐭 𝐒𝐮𝐫𝐢 𝐇𝐨𝐬𝐩𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐲 𝐆𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐩, didn’t grow up on the margins. 𝐇𝐞 𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐰 𝐮𝐩 𝐢𝐧 𝐚 𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐟𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐲. But 𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬𝐧’𝐭 𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐭𝐞𝐜𝐭 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐭𝐲 when the country doesn’t want to see it.

𝐇𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 𝐝𝐫𝐚𝐠. He found voice. He 𝐟𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐠𝐮𝐭𝐬 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝 𝐩𝐨𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐲 into a brand. 𝐍𝐨𝐰 𝐡𝐞 𝐫𝐮𝐧𝐬 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐋𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐭. Loudly. Clearly. Openly.

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐰𝐞𝐞𝐤, 𝐨𝐧 𝑻𝒂𝒍𝒌 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝑲𝒖𝒏𝒂𝒍 𝑽𝒂𝒔𝒖𝒅𝒆𝒗𝒂, we talk about what it means to stop hiding: 𝐚𝐭 𝐡𝐨𝐦𝐞, 𝐢𝐧 𝐛𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬, 𝐢𝐧 𝐩𝐮𝐛𝐥𝐢𝐜.

Full episode drops Thursday.

With love, pride, and togetherness, we begin Pride Month at The LaLiT.

This year, the Pride Parade lit up the iconic Connaught Place in New Delhi — a powerful celebration of colour, joy, and unapologetic self-expression. As the city’s historic heart pulsed with unity and freedom, it echoed The LaLiT’s enduring belief: that love knows no bounds.

Here’s to celebrating pure love — today, and every single day.
#PureLove #PrideMonth #PrideMonth2025 #TheLaLiT #TheLaLiTNewDelhi

Art at The LaLiT | When you step into The LaLiT New Delhi, you enter a realm where art embraces hospitality. It’s not merely a hotel; it’s a sanctuary for art enthusiasts. The moment you walk through the grand entrance, you’re welcomed by unique pieces you’ll find the marvellous work of M.F. Husain,Satish Gujral,Lalita Vakil,Paresh Maity and  Naresh Kapuria.

The LaLiT is truly an art lover’s haven. At this hotel, one can easily spend an entire day meandering through halls echoed with the whispers of artistic mastery. Here, art isn’t just displayed; it lives and breathes, offering an escape into a realm where creativity knows no bounds.

To know more, follow the link in our bio #TheLaLiT #ArtAtTheLaLiT

Meet Adwitya Bhatnagar, pianist at The LaLiT New Delhi.
Diagnosed with autism at the age of six, Adwitya’s journey is one of resilience, talent, and quiet brilliance. Today, he holds an eighth-grade certification in piano from Trinity School, UK — and continues to inspire us every day.

At The LaLiT, we celebrate diverse voices, unique journeys, and the power of inclusion. We are proud to be a safe space where talent thrives, and everyone belongs.

#TheLaLiT #InclusiveIndia #Neurodiversity #TalentWithoutLabels #AutismAcceptance #SkillsThatInspire #TheLalitNewDelhi #PureLove

Valedictory Function – The LaLiT Suri Hospitality School

Highlights from Mr. K.B. Kachru’s Address @kbkachru 

At the valedictory function for the 3rd-year students, Mr. K.B. Kachru shared inspiring insights on leadership, consistency, and pride in one’s work.
He emphasized that “big things come from doing small things right”.

Applauding the 100% placement record, he stressed that talent is the key to the hospitality industry’s future.

He also praised The LaLiT Group’s commitment to sustainability and LGBTQ inclusion, calling their vision and community service truly inspiring.
“Leadership is about how many leaders you create,” he concluded, encouraging students to value their journey and lead with purpose.

#thelalitsurihospitalityschool #kbkachru #hospitality
